{
  "stem": "19198.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Another impression, of course, was the New York subway, which was so much more extensive than the other-- only other subway that I'd experienced, in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I remember it specifically from being told how to get to Brooklyn from the Bronx by subway, because a family from Eberbach lived in the-- in Brooklyn, and they invited me to have lunch with them.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, they were not Jewish, and they had arranged for a kosher lunch at their home.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I successfully transacted my trip on the-- on the subway, changing once or twice, and got to Brooklyn, found my way to their home.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I was very proud of that accomplishment.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Their name was Kadel.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "K-A-D-E-L.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Mrs.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Kadel was a-- nee Wieprecht.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "W-I-E-P-R-E-C-H-T, which was her family in-- in Eberbach.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, why did so many Germans come to the United States?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Opportunity.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were fairly well informed by correspondence and by reading the papers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And yes, they asked for specifics of what was happening in Eberbach.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They-- they knew it was a-- a terrible mess.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was something to worry about, and certainly understood my coming.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were trying to bring over any of their immediate family, and successfully did so.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We stayed in New York three days, spent one day in Washington to sightsee in Washington, which we did all five of us together, and then took a Baltimore and Ohio train from-- an overnight train from Washington to Cincinnati.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Was-- had all the-- the problems of an overnight coach trip.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
